The Turkish central bank is estimated
to have sold between $300 and $400 million, Tufan Comert,
strategist at Garanti Securities, said by telephone.  The bank sold dollars for liras in the Istanbul market
today for a second day, two traders with knowledge of the sales
said on condition of anonymity.  To contact the reporter on this story:
